    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>Chaos isn't a pit. Chaos is a ladder. Many who try to climb it fail and never get to try again. The fall breaks them. And some, are given a chance to climb. They refuse, they cling to the realm or the gods or love. Illusions. Only the ladder is real. The climb is all there is.\n\n<br><br>Little Bajju has decided to climb the ladder of chaos.\n\nHe starts at 0th step and has to reach exactly the nth step.\nHe cannot go beyond the nth step or below the 0th step or the fall will break him.\nEach step <b>'i'</b> of the ladder, has some power of chaos <b>'p[i]'</b> associated with it.\nAt each step <b>'i'</b> he has a choice. He could either proceed to the next step <b>'i+1'</b> or he could use the power of chaos and jump to the step <b>'i+p[i]'</b>.\nAny move or jump that results to reaching a step greater than n or less than 0 is invalid and will lead to Bajju's fall.\n\n<br><br>Little Bajju's caring friend Dwij wants to help him out. He wants to find out the minimum number of steps Bajju will need to reach to the top of the ladder <b>(nth step, starting from 0th step)</b>. Can you help Dwij in helping Little Bajju ?</p>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>\n<ul>\n<li>The first line contains<b> 't'</b>, the number of testcases</li>\n<li>Each testcase consists of 2 lines.</li>\n<li>The first line contains the integer <b>n</b>.</li>\n<li>The next line consists of <b>n</b> space separated integer, denoting the power of chaos <b>p[i]</b> of each step from <b>0 to n-1</b></li></ul>.</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print the minimum number of jumps required to reach the nth step for each testcase on a newline.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>t</b> \u2264 <b>1000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>20</b></li>\n<li><b>-15</b> \u2264 <b>p[i]</b> \u2264 <b>15</b></li>\n<li><b>p[i]!=0</b></li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n1\n10\n5 1 1 1 6 -1 1 1 1 1\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n3\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> Using optimum strategy Little Bajju goes +5 from Step 0 to Step 5, -1 from Step 5 to Step 4 and +6 from Step 4 to Step 10. Hence 3 steps are required.</p>",
